From: John Rogers [mailto:jnrogers(-at-)verizon.net] 
Subject: Re: [T2] RE:Gas heater

 

Here is something to consider. When I installed an Eberspacher BN4 in my
1970 bus, I connected the on-off switch to a room thermostat rather than s
simple switch on the dash. This has worked well. When camping I can set the
thermostat to a come-on temperature and go to sleep knowing that I won't
have to get up and turn anything on if the temperature inside drops too
much.
